WEBVTT

00:02.970 --> 00:06.105
♪♪

00:06.107 --> 00:09.775
Ah, here she is --
my beautiful daughter,

00:09.777 --> 00:14.346
up and ready to explore
this wonderful day!

00:15.383 --> 00:18.384
Mom, I swear, if you keep up
with this fake-happy crap,

00:18.386 --> 00:19.952
I'm gonna lock myself
in my room.

00:21.455 --> 00:23.722
Did you hear that,
muffin?

00:23.724 --> 00:26.158
She's not very happy.

00:26.160 --> 00:28.027
"What?

00:28.029 --> 00:31.630
Maybe if I lick her face,
that'll help."

00:31.632 --> 00:34.967
Oh, muffin,
you always know what to do!

00:34.969 --> 00:36.568
[ Smooching ]

00:36.570 --> 00:39.405
Ugh! Even the dog
is embarrassed.

00:39.407 --> 00:40.739
[ Sighs ]

00:40.741 --> 00:42.141
Eve, you know something?

00:42.143 --> 00:44.977
I know you're upset about
not getting into West Point,

00:44.979 --> 00:46.345
but you can always
reapply.

00:46.347 --> 00:48.347
Oh, yes,
because it felt<i> so</i> good

00:48.349 --> 00:49.882
when they told me
they didn't want me,

00:49.884 --> 00:53.018
I just want them to say it
again and again and again.

00:53.020 --> 00:54.219
Hey, look
at the bright side.

00:54.221 --> 00:56.355
You got into a lot
of other really great colleges.

00:56.357 --> 00:58.057
Right, so why
can't I just move on?

00:58.059 --> 01:00.159
I mean, if dad had
turned you down for marriage,

01:00.161 --> 01:01.994
I'm sure there were
plenty of other losers

01:01.996 --> 01:04.296
you would have loved
to spend your life with, right?

01:05.199 --> 01:07.066
I don't know what
your father's been telling you,

01:07.068 --> 01:09.001
but<i> he</i> asked<i> me.</i>

01:09.003 --> 01:11.904
So your life's been perfect.
Congratulations.

01:11.906 --> 01:13.505
Come on, come on, honey.
It's winter break!

01:13.507 --> 01:15.574
Don't you want to get out
of the house and do something?

01:15.576 --> 01:17.109
Mm, nope, I'm good.

01:17.111 --> 01:18.544
The shows may change,

01:18.545 --> 01:19.978
but the butt placement
will stay the same.

01:23.217 --> 01:24.550
Mm.
Wha--

01:24.552 --> 01:26.418
wow. The weirdest thing
just happened.

01:26.420 --> 01:28.954
A bird flew in
and took your doughnut.

01:31.625 --> 01:35.194
All these crumbs you see
are a result of the struggle.

01:37.965 --> 01:40.032
I'm worried about Eve.
Ah.

01:40.034 --> 01:41.967
You know, she hasn't
snapped out of her funk,

01:41.969 --> 01:44.069
and she just sits in there
on the couch all day.

01:44.071 --> 01:46.138
The deadlines for the colleges
she did get into

01:46.140 --> 01:47.239
are coming up
really fast.

01:47.241 --> 01:49.208
So you think
it's time I stepped in.

01:49.210 --> 01:50.442
Well, I think
we should talk about it,

01:50.444 --> 01:51.743
come up with a plan,
and then --

01:51.745 --> 01:52.811
I got this.

01:52.813 --> 01:54.913
Well, honey, wait --
uh, just...

01:54.915 --> 01:56.248
Be gentle, okay?

01:56.250 --> 01:57.649
She's really fragile
right now.

01:57.651 --> 01:58.584
Honey, you know me.

01:58.586 --> 02:00.452
Okay.

02:00.454 --> 02:03.422
Eve. Eve, get your ass
off the couch.

02:03.424 --> 02:05.991
You're going to work
with me.

02:07.595 --> 02:08.894
What?

02:08.896 --> 02:11.396
Yeah. Your mom's tired
of you moping. So am I.

02:11.398 --> 02:13.298
Either get ready right now
or I'm taking you in your pjs.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.467
Let's go. Come on. I'm not gonna
go to work with you, dad.

02:15.469 --> 02:16.802
Okay, fine.
That's a good choice.

02:16.804 --> 02:18.770
Get some duct tape,
I'll get a hand truck. Let's go.

02:18.772 --> 02:20.239
All right, all right, all right.
Fine, fine, fine.

02:20.241 --> 02:23.709
Can I at least finish
the cheerios in my robe pocket?

02:24.979 --> 02:26.745
Okay, fine!

02:26.747 --> 02:29.748
I'll go, but I'm not gonna
do anything or talk to anybody.

02:29.750 --> 02:32.451
That's<i> my</i> job.
You got to work up to that.

02:32.453 --> 02:33.952
Go on.
Come on, come on, come on!

02:33.954 --> 02:35.454
Let's go!
I got to get going here!

02:35.456 --> 02:36.872
That was gentle?

02:36.873 --> 02:38.289
Honey, you knew
what you were getting into

02:38.292 --> 02:39.858
when you asked me
to marry you.

02:39.860 --> 02:42.161
I --

02:42.163 --> 02:45.164
-- captions by Vitac --

02:45.166 --> 02:48.233
♪♪

02:50.704 --> 02:53.272
Okay, I came to work with you.
Can I leave now?

02:53.274 --> 02:56.875
With that attitude,
you'll fit right in around here.

02:56.877 --> 02:58.844
What are we doing
in the service center?

02:58.846 --> 03:02.381
Looking for my newest
and least favorite employee.

03:02.383 --> 03:04.616
Hope you're not talking
about<i> me.</i>

03:09.356 --> 03:11.456
Hey, Eve.

03:11.458 --> 03:12.958
Hi, Mr. Leonard.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.459
Well,
what brings you here?

03:14.461 --> 03:16.595
It's "bring your pain-in-
the ass-daughter to work" day.

03:17.831 --> 03:20.799
When I'm sad, that's the kind
of stuff my dad says to me.

03:20.801 --> 03:23.168
Listen, I'm not getting
any repair reports upstairs,

03:23.170 --> 03:25.504
so I can't get reimbursement
from the manufacturers

03:25.506 --> 03:26.505
for the warranty work.

03:26.507 --> 03:27.739
Are you using the iPad?

03:27.741 --> 03:30.509
You mean that fancy
etch a sketch thing?

03:30.511 --> 03:33.979
Yeah, the $700
etch a sketch thing.

03:33.981 --> 03:35.747
When I hired you
to fill in,

03:35.749 --> 03:37.349
you said you knew
how to use one of these.

03:37.351 --> 03:38.350
I do.
Right.

03:38.352 --> 03:39.885
Makes a great coaster.

03:45.392 --> 03:46.858
It also makes
a good camera.

03:46.860 --> 03:48.694
You take a picture
of the repairs you're doing,

03:48.696 --> 03:51.163
then you send one up
to the server and cc it to me.

03:51.165 --> 03:54.433
Whoa, whoa. Slow down,
Harry Potter, huh?

03:54.435 --> 03:55.567
I got a better idea.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.336
Why don't I bring my camera to work?
Okay.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.770
I'll take a picture of the job.
Oh, good. Yeah.

03:58.772 --> 04:00.038
I'll go down the drugstore.
Right.

04:00.040 --> 04:01.406
I'll get the picture
developed.

04:01.408 --> 04:04.276
I come back here, I take my pen,
I fill out the report.

04:04.278 --> 04:06.511
What could be simpler
than that?

04:06.513 --> 04:08.680
Using the iPad.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.716
Is this how
he motivates people?

04:10.718 --> 04:12.884
Eh, he's pretty much
all stick and no carrot.

04:12.886 --> 04:13.952
Know what I mean?

04:13.954 --> 04:15.587
You know,
I like this kid.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.623
Good.
Why don't you keep her?

04:17.625 --> 04:20.859
Listen, as a matter of fact,
Eve, I got a job for you.

04:20.861 --> 04:22.928
I want you to teach Joe here
how to use this coaster.

04:22.930 --> 04:25.364
Aw, come on.
Don't make the kid do that.

04:25.366 --> 04:26.632
Wouldn't you rather
be at the roller rink

04:26.634 --> 04:28.267
or maybe
at the malt shop?

04:28.269 --> 04:30.402
[ Vocalizing ]

04:30.404 --> 04:32.371
Uh...No.
I've got time.

04:32.373 --> 04:35.407
Archie and Jughead
are busy, anyway.

04:35.409 --> 04:37.709
Listen,
from now on, Joe,

04:37.711 --> 04:39.478
my daughter's
gonna be your gal Friday.

04:39.480 --> 04:41.380
It's, like,
an 80-year-old reference.

04:41.382 --> 04:43.548
I'm sure you'll understand it,
all right?

04:45.619 --> 04:47.786
Okay, look,
so, here's what you got to do.

04:47.788 --> 04:48.620
[ Scoffs ]

04:48.622 --> 04:51.056
You just
press this button...

04:51.058 --> 04:52.824
[ Camera clicks ] And
there's your picture.

04:52.826 --> 04:55.494
It sounds complicated.

04:55.496 --> 04:57.729
How do you get through life
not knowing this stuff?

04:57.731 --> 04:58.964
Quite well, thank you.

04:58.966 --> 05:00.832
You know, I like life simple.
That's why I'm a mechanic.

05:00.834 --> 05:02.467
Look --
something's broke,

05:02.469 --> 05:05.404
you work on it, you fix it,
and at the end of the day,

05:05.406 --> 05:07.272
you felt like
you've done something.

05:07.274 --> 05:09.608
Yeah, well,
if you take a picture of it,

05:09.610 --> 05:11.843
at the end of the day,
you'll have a job.

05:13.781 --> 05:15.113
All right,
look, I'll give it a try.

05:15.115 --> 05:16.682
Look,
I'll tell you what --

05:16.684 --> 05:19.685
you taught<i> me</i> something.
I'm gonna teach<i> you</i> something.

05:19.687 --> 05:21.753
You know the candy machine
in the hall? Yeah.

05:21.755 --> 05:25.657
You tip it all the way to right,
free kit kats.

05:25.659 --> 05:27.092
Want me to show you?

05:27.094 --> 05:28.160
Hellz yeah!

05:28.162 --> 05:31.596
♪♪

05:31.598 --> 05:34.533
[ Sighs ]

05:34.535 --> 05:35.834
Hey, babe.

05:35.836 --> 05:38.870
You know,
I'm feeling really sick.

05:38.872 --> 05:41.773
I probably shouldn't have dinner
with Kyle and Mandy tonight.

05:41.775 --> 05:43.175
Stupid flu, you know?

05:43.177 --> 05:44.543
[ Chuckles ]

05:44.545 --> 05:46.878
Well,<i> that's</i> how
you're gonna fake being sick?

05:46.880 --> 05:48.680
Those acting classes
at the community center

05:48.682 --> 05:50.716
are<i> not</i> paying off.

05:50.718 --> 05:53.185
Come on.
Mandy is my sister, okay?

05:53.187 --> 05:54.720
I want the four of us
to be close.

05:54.722 --> 05:56.822
Can't you just do stuff
with<i> her?</i>

05:56.824 --> 05:59.391
I mean, I like Kyle,
but we have nothing in common.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.460
At least your dad
gives me material

06:01.462 --> 06:03.695
for the message boards
on huffington post.

06:03.697 --> 06:05.797
[ Knock on door ]

06:05.799 --> 06:07.666
Look, I think
Kyle's in this family to stay,

06:07.668 --> 06:10.302
so it would be great if you found
some way to connect with him.

06:10.304 --> 06:11.703
[ Scoffs ] You know what?
You're right.

06:11.705 --> 06:13.071
This is important to you,
so I will try hard.

06:13.073 --> 06:13.905
Thank you.

06:13.907 --> 06:15.073
[ Laughs ]

06:15.075 --> 06:17.142
Those acting classes
<i> are</i> paying off.

06:19.213 --> 06:20.712
Hey. Come on in.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.814
Thanks. And as good guests,
we brought you guys a gift.

06:22.816 --> 06:24.649
Kristin: Ooh!
Oh, my god.

06:24.651 --> 06:26.752
That's "steel angel", volume 1.
This is a classic.

06:26.754 --> 06:29.154
Uh, actually,
the<i> wine</i> is the gift.

06:30.591 --> 06:33.859
Brought this to read
in case I got bored.

06:33.861 --> 06:36.228
I didn't know
you liked comic books, Kyle.

06:36.230 --> 06:37.362
[ Chuckles ]

06:37.364 --> 06:38.997
Both: "Graphic novels."

06:38.999 --> 06:40.832
You know, I love
how the characters

06:40.834 --> 06:42.901
grapple with the dilemma
of vigilantism

06:42.903 --> 06:44.169
in a nonlinear format.

06:44.171 --> 06:46.872
Yeah. And I love
how they can pick up cars.

06:46.874 --> 06:49.441
Hey, I've got Frank Miller's
"Dark Knight Returns" set

06:49.443 --> 06:50.575
bagged and boarded.

06:50.577 --> 06:51.676
Do you want to see it?

06:51.678 --> 06:52.811
Can I?
Go.

06:55.349 --> 06:58.083
I, uh, didn't know
Ryan was a comic book nerd, too.

06:58.085 --> 07:00.886
Yeah, I didn't, either,
until<i> after</i> the wedding.

07:00.888 --> 07:03.922
Hey, I'm glad that they found
something that they both like.

07:03.924 --> 07:05.690
It'll make it easier
for us to hang out more.

07:05.692 --> 07:07.926
More? Oh, I thought
this was a one-and-done.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.628
Cheers.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.930
What are you talking about?
W-we're sisters.

07:11.932 --> 07:14.866
Yeah! We're lucky.
We don't<i> have</i> to hang out.

07:14.868 --> 07:16.802
Hey, um,
let's get this dinner rolling.

07:16.804 --> 07:18.970
Kyle and I have plans
with friends later.

07:23.877 --> 07:24.810
Hi.

07:24.812 --> 07:25.744
Hey.

07:25.746 --> 07:27.546
[ Door closes ]
Ooh!

07:27.548 --> 07:30.916
Salami, mortadella,
provolone --

07:30.918 --> 07:32.617
that looks like
your happy sandwich.

07:32.619 --> 07:34.319
Yeah.

07:34.321 --> 07:38.056
Be a lot happier if somebody
had remembered to buy mustard.

07:38.058 --> 07:39.624
But I did buy you dinner.

07:39.626 --> 07:41.460
So why are you
having a sandwich?

07:41.462 --> 07:43.061
I told you --
I'm going over to Joe's.

07:43.063 --> 07:45.230
We're gonna put a 428
in his GTO.

07:45.232 --> 07:46.765
Well,
if all that car gibberish

07:46.767 --> 07:48.233
means I don't
have to make dinner,

07:48.235 --> 07:50.469
then whoo-hoo!

07:50.471 --> 07:51.903
You're having
the happy sandwich.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.638
Does that mean things went well
at Outdoor Man?

07:53.640 --> 07:55.640
Yeah, Eve's back
among the living.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.609
You know,
we sell guns and ammo,

07:57.611 --> 08:00.979
but Outdoor Man
is a place of healing.

08:00.981 --> 08:02.113
Thank god.

08:02.115 --> 08:03.648
It's hard
to feel like a good mom

08:03.650 --> 08:05.450
when your kid
spends all day in her bathrobe

08:05.452 --> 08:07.786
eating breakfast
out of her pockets.

08:07.788 --> 08:09.354
Well, she's back
to her old self.

08:09.356 --> 08:12.123
She's having so much fun
at work, I let her stay late.

08:12.125 --> 08:13.525
Chuck's bringing her home
right now.

08:13.527 --> 08:14.926
Well, thank you, Mike.

08:14.928 --> 08:17.362
Maybe now I can get Eve to
sit down and pick out a college.

08:17.364 --> 08:18.497
Hey, Evie.

08:18.499 --> 08:19.664
Good evening, people.

08:19.666 --> 08:20.499
[ Laughs ]

08:20.501 --> 08:22.000
Hey, Evie.
How was work?

08:22.002 --> 08:23.335
Great.

08:23.337 --> 08:26.638
On lunch break, I won 8 bucks
shooting dice with Felipe.

08:26.640 --> 08:28.273
You won 8 bucks?

08:28.275 --> 08:30.375
Go get me some mustard.

08:30.377 --> 08:32.010
Joe was actually
really helpful.

08:32.012 --> 08:33.645
He gave me a ton of advice
on college.

08:33.647 --> 08:35.847
Oh, that's nice.
Where did Joe go to college?

08:35.849 --> 08:38.016
He<i> didn't.</i>

08:38.018 --> 08:40.051
Oh, boy.

08:40.053 --> 08:41.219
Yeah.

08:41.221 --> 08:42.787
And<i> I'm</i> not going to,
either.

08:42.789 --> 08:44.122
I'm gonna be a mechanic.

08:46.527 --> 08:48.360
[ Laughs nervously ]
Uh-oh.

08:52.633 --> 08:53.732
♪♪

08:53.734 --> 08:55.233
Mike, I don't care
what this Joe says.

08:55.235 --> 08:57.903
She is not gonna be a mechanic.
She is going to college.

08:57.905 --> 08:59.455
She's a little lost
right now.

08:59.456 --> 09:01.006
She's just jumping at
the first thing that came along.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.807
Lucky I didn't take her
to a men's club.

09:02.809 --> 09:03.909
[ Laughs ]

09:03.911 --> 09:05.677
We need
to go talk to her!

09:05.679 --> 09:06.912
No, no, no, no.
Wait.

09:06.914 --> 09:08.146
It took her two weeks
to get off the couch.

09:08.148 --> 09:10.181
Let's not do anything to put her
back on the couch, honey.

09:10.183 --> 09:11.550
Oh, so<i> we</i> can't talk
to Eve,

09:11.552 --> 09:13.585
but Joe's gonna have her ear
for eight hours tomorrow.

09:13.587 --> 09:15.020
I'm sure
that'll turn out well.

09:15.022 --> 09:16.154
All right, all right,
tonight, when I go over there,

09:16.156 --> 09:17.389
I'll talk to Joe
and tell him

09:17.391 --> 09:19.157
to keep his opinions to himself,
and I'll do that

09:19.159 --> 09:22.494
while I've got the engine
on a hoist right over his head.

09:22.496 --> 09:24.396
♪♪

09:27.868 --> 09:29.100
Hey, Mike!
Hey, Joe.

09:29.102 --> 09:30.368
Glad you're here.

09:30.370 --> 09:34.339
Now I got somebody to bitch to
about my idiot boss.

09:34.341 --> 09:36.274
Well,
what a coincidence,

09:36.276 --> 09:39.578
'cause I've got an employee
who's acting like a jackass.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.413
Is it Felipe?

09:41.415 --> 09:44.082
Did you have a long conversation
with my daughter?

09:44.084 --> 09:45.083
Oh, yeah.
Let me tell you something.

09:45.085 --> 09:46.117
That girl
has opened my eyes

09:46.119 --> 09:48.186
to a whole new world
of technology.

09:48.188 --> 09:49.854
Let me show you
this video I found.

09:49.856 --> 09:50.855
Look at this.

09:50.857 --> 09:52.090
You see this here?
Look at this.

09:52.092 --> 09:55.293
It's a monkey
giving a cat a bath.

09:55.295 --> 09:56.227
I mean, it's --

09:56.229 --> 09:58.263
how does that friendship
even start?

09:58.265 --> 10:00.298
You know, Eve's got
quite a future ahead of her,

10:00.300 --> 10:03.201
and what I'd like to do is let
her parents do the parenting.

10:03.203 --> 10:05.403
W-well, what's that
supposed to mean?

10:05.405 --> 10:06.972
She comes home
after talking to you

10:06.974 --> 10:08.239
and doesn't want
to go to college.

10:08.241 --> 10:09.641
She wants
to become a mechanic.

10:09.643 --> 10:11.743
So what's the big deal, Mike?
College isn't for everybody.

10:11.745 --> 10:12.911
You know,
that's the thing

10:12.913 --> 10:14.379
with you pointy-headed elitists,
you know?

10:14.381 --> 10:15.981
You're so far up
in your ivory tower,

10:15.983 --> 10:17.148
you can't see
what's going on.

10:17.150 --> 10:18.817
Elitist?
What tipped you off?

10:18.819 --> 10:21.252
That I brought a sandwich
in a bag?

10:21.254 --> 10:23.388
You know, you Ivy league guys
are all alike.

10:23.390 --> 10:25.056
You all think
you're so great.

10:25.058 --> 10:26.324
You know something?

10:26.326 --> 10:28.326
I'll bet the only time
you've ever been in a tent is...

10:28.328 --> 10:29.894
When you occupied
wall street.

10:31.164 --> 10:34.265
I'll have you know I did
a photo shoot in the Himalayas.

10:34.267 --> 10:37.102
Look, I slept
in the carcass of a dead goat.

10:37.104 --> 10:39.137
Let me guess --
the goat was cashmere.

10:40.273 --> 10:41.706
Damn it.
Yeah, it was.

10:42.943 --> 10:45.443
My daughter's dream has
always been to go to West Point.

10:45.445 --> 10:47.746
And just recently,
she got rejected.

10:47.748 --> 10:51.316
Oh, I'm sorry.
I -- I didn't know that.

10:51.318 --> 10:52.917
You know, she's real vulnerable
right now.

10:52.919 --> 10:55.420
Obviously<i> real</i> vulnerable --
she's taking advice from<i> you.</i>

10:55.422 --> 10:56.688
Whoa, whoa, whoa, Mike.

10:56.690 --> 10:58.923
I get it -- that's why
you want her to go to college,

10:58.925 --> 11:00.959
so she can be
a big Harvard snob,

11:00.961 --> 11:02.460
like<i> you</i> are.

11:02.462 --> 11:03.428
That's right. She --

11:03.430 --> 11:05.530
what? No! No, no.

11:05.532 --> 11:07.265
I just want her
to go to college.

11:07.267 --> 11:10.335
Can we get to the part where
your head is under the engine?

11:10.337 --> 11:12.370
♪♪

11:14.708 --> 11:17.008
Well, my "Avenger" comics
would be worth more

11:17.010 --> 11:19.678
if I hadn't drawn devil horns
on Ultron.

11:19.680 --> 11:21.646
He is not
a nice person.

11:21.648 --> 11:23.314
Technically,
he's not a person.

11:23.316 --> 11:25.717
That is no excuse
for that kind of behavior.

11:25.719 --> 11:27.385
You know what --
they're having an exhibition

11:27.387 --> 11:28.720
of early '30s graphic novels
at the museum.

11:28.722 --> 11:29.954
Why don't we all
go check it out?

11:29.956 --> 11:31.589
No.

11:32.726 --> 11:34.125
Why not?

11:34.127 --> 11:35.660
I thought you wanted to spend
more time with your sister.

11:35.662 --> 11:36.995
Mm, yeah,
then I found out

11:36.997 --> 11:38.730
that she doesn't want
to hang out with<i> me,</i>

11:38.732 --> 11:41.166
so enjoy
your cartoon talk<i> now,</i>

11:41.168 --> 11:43.568
because this is
a one-and-done.

11:47.407 --> 11:49.574
Uh, hey, do you want to see
my Captain America shield?

11:49.576 --> 11:52.610
Uh, do you want to see the biggest
smile you've ever seen in your life?

11:56.349 --> 11:59.350
Okay. I didn't mean
to hurt your feelings.

11:59.352 --> 12:01.519
[ Scoffs ] You didn't.
I feel the same way.

12:01.521 --> 12:04.656
The only reason we had you over
is because Ryan made me.

12:04.658 --> 12:07.492
I was gonna, like, fake the flu
to try to get out of it, so...

12:07.494 --> 12:09.027
See?
We're on the same page.

12:09.029 --> 12:11.396
[ Scoffs ]
I was kidding.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.665
I was really
looking forward to this.

12:13.667 --> 12:16.334
What is so terrible
about spending time with me?

12:16.336 --> 12:17.535
[ Chuckling ] Nothing.

12:17.537 --> 12:20.872
Although, all this yelling at me
isn't superduper fun.

12:20.874 --> 12:22.407
When you were little,

12:22.409 --> 12:24.909
we used to do
a lot of things together.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.244
I know,
and then you had a kid

12:26.246 --> 12:28.480
and you thought
it suddenly made you a mom.

12:29.783 --> 12:31.116
Yeah, it kind of did.

12:31.118 --> 12:33.551
Yeah, but not<i> my</i> mom.

12:33.553 --> 12:36.888
You were always all,
"be responsible. Be careful.

12:36.890 --> 12:38.923
Put your shirt
back on."

12:38.925 --> 12:40.091
Okay, fine.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.559
I'm sorry
I tried so hard

12:41.561 --> 12:44.596
to keep you from making mistakes
all of those years.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.631
Hey.
I forgive you.

12:48.368 --> 12:51.569
You know what? Just -- just go
have fun with your friends.

12:51.571 --> 12:52.537
Thanks. We will.

12:52.539 --> 12:54.305
Ohh!
And dinner was delish.

12:54.307 --> 12:56.141
Thank you so much
for wrapping it up by 8:00.

12:56.143 --> 12:58.610
Hey, Kyle!
Let's go!

13:01.581 --> 13:04.549
Ryan said I could wear this
for the rest of the night!

13:08.555 --> 13:09.754
Okay.

13:09.756 --> 13:11.222
Just in the car.

13:11.224 --> 13:14.359
♪♪

13:17.798 --> 13:18.830
Hi, dad.

13:18.832 --> 13:20.832
It's "Mr. Baxter."

13:20.834 --> 13:22.567
Um, I'm gonna go
down to the garage.

13:22.569 --> 13:23.635
Joe says
he's gonna teach me

13:23.637 --> 13:26.237
how to heat a can of beans
on a engine block.

13:26.239 --> 13:28.473
Oh, great --
a mechanic<i> and</i> a hobo.

13:28.475 --> 13:29.941
No wonder you like
spending time with him.

13:29.943 --> 13:31.676
Actually, I don't want you
going down there today.

13:31.678 --> 13:33.745
I want you to spend some time
up here in accounting.

13:33.747 --> 13:35.580
Why? I already know
what I want to do.

13:35.582 --> 13:37.332
I'm gonna be a mechanic.

13:37.333 --> 13:39.083
I want you to experience a lot
of different things, honey.

13:39.085 --> 13:40.518
Yeah, but accounting?

13:40.520 --> 13:45.423
Yeah. Accountants are like
the mechanics of numbers.

13:45.425 --> 13:48.126
Yeah, but the nerds
of everything else.

13:48.128 --> 13:49.661
I bet none of them
know how to tune an engine.

13:49.663 --> 13:51.362
You don't know
how to tune an engine.

13:51.364 --> 13:52.664
Well, so I'll learn.

13:52.666 --> 13:54.532
You've been down in
my service center for one day.

13:54.534 --> 13:56.601
What's your sudden fascination
becoming a mechanic?

13:56.603 --> 13:58.703
Well, because
it just makes sense, okay?

13:58.705 --> 14:00.672
It's simple -- something's
broken, and you fix it.

14:00.674 --> 14:02.774
You don't understand,
dad.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.977
Oh, I think I do.

14:09.816 --> 14:11.683
♪♪

14:12.853 --> 14:14.385
Hey, Eve. Eve.

14:14.387 --> 14:17.222
Don't worry. I'll go down
to accounting in a second.

14:17.224 --> 14:20.058
Unless you've decided to send me
someplace even<i> more</i> boring.

14:21.161 --> 14:23.761
I don't think
such a place exists.

14:25.232 --> 14:26.531
Wait a minute.
What is this? What is this?

14:26.533 --> 14:27.732
Is this
one of those bombs

14:27.734 --> 14:29.968
you got to try to dismantle
with the fuse?

14:29.970 --> 14:31.336
I got a ticking clock.

14:31.338 --> 14:33.371
Is it the blue wire? Is it the red wire?
I don't know!

14:33.373 --> 14:35.874
At the last minute, it goes
right down, and you click --

14:35.876 --> 14:36.975
it didn't blow up.
Why not?

14:36.977 --> 14:38.309
Because I'm tom cruise

14:38.311 --> 14:39.711
and I got six more
of these movies to do.

14:39.713 --> 14:40.778
That's why.

14:43.817 --> 14:45.650
It's the alternator
from the atv.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.352
Joe said it's shot.
He went to go get another one.

14:47.354 --> 14:49.587
Yeah? Why don't you just use
the one out of the snowmobile?

14:49.589 --> 14:52.523
Um, because it's from the atv.
That part wouldn't work.

14:52.525 --> 14:53.758
Works
in the snowmobile.

14:53.760 --> 14:56.728
Yeah, well, you can't
just pull a part off one machine

14:56.730 --> 14:58.730
and use it
to fix a different machine.

14:58.732 --> 15:00.932
And you can't just a pull a part
off somebody's else life

15:00.934 --> 15:02.901
to make<i> your</i> life work,
either.

15:04.271 --> 15:06.237
Clever.

15:06.239 --> 15:07.605
It's a metaphor.

15:07.607 --> 15:09.741
I learned about that
in college.

15:09.743 --> 15:11.876
[ Scoffs ]
All right. Fine.

15:11.878 --> 15:13.011
I give up.

15:13.013 --> 15:14.879
I won't be a mechanic.

15:14.881 --> 15:16.347
I'll go to college.

15:16.349 --> 15:17.782
Whatever
makes you guys happy.

15:17.784 --> 15:19.450
It's not about
making us happy.

15:19.452 --> 15:21.085
You know
what this is really about?

15:21.087 --> 15:23.221
Making<i> you</i> happy.

15:23.223 --> 15:24.689
Hey, what brings you
to the service area,

15:24.691 --> 15:27.225
professor elbow patch?

15:27.227 --> 15:28.927
I'm having a conversation
with my daughter.

15:28.929 --> 15:29.928
Give us just a minute.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.729
Listen, it's about
making you happy --

15:31.731 --> 15:33.698
dad, what if I never find
something in my life

15:33.700 --> 15:35.266
that means as much
as West Point did?

15:35.268 --> 15:37.602
Whoa,
Mike, Mike, Mike, Mike.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.071
Let me step in here a minute.
I got some pull with the kid.

15:40.073 --> 15:41.272
Do you?

15:42.709 --> 15:44.375
Sure. Let me go
check on the beans.

15:44.377 --> 15:45.877
Check on the beans,
yeah.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.247
Look, I didn't always want
to be a mechanic, okay?

15:49.249 --> 15:51.616
When I was growing up, I had
a whole different set of dreams.

15:51.618 --> 15:54.619
Yeah, but, Joe,
we can't all be ballerinas.

15:56.923 --> 15:58.056
No, I...

15:58.058 --> 15:59.824
I wanted to be
a comedian.

16:00.727 --> 16:03.361
You would have had better luck
being a ballerina, pal.

16:05.832 --> 16:08.800
Anyway, I quit my job.
I drove to Denver.

16:08.802 --> 16:11.903
I started bugging the club owner
to give me stage time.

16:11.905 --> 16:12.971
Were you any good?

16:12.973 --> 16:16.307
I-I think I was
too hip for the room.

16:16.309 --> 16:18.009
What does that mean?

16:18.011 --> 16:19.510
He sucked!

16:21.181 --> 16:22.914
Anyway, I couldn't get
any stage time,

16:22.916 --> 16:25.416
but the owner had this crappy
'65 Chevelle that didn't run,

16:25.418 --> 16:26.818
so he paid me
to work on it.

16:26.820 --> 16:29.120
Next thing you know, other guys
are bringing me their cars,

16:29.122 --> 16:31.089
and in five years,
I had my own shop.

16:31.091 --> 16:31.823
Huh.

16:31.825 --> 16:32.991
That's a cool story.

16:32.993 --> 16:34.525
That's a good story.
It's life, actually.

16:34.527 --> 16:36.794
Sometimes, the things
you're meant to do find<i> you.</i>

16:36.796 --> 16:38.129
[ Sighs ] All right.

16:38.131 --> 16:40.131
So maybe I give
the accounting department a day

16:40.133 --> 16:41.332
just to cross that
off the list.

16:41.334 --> 16:44.202
You might be surprised.
They're pretty cool up there.

16:44.204 --> 16:47.505
Sometimes,
they round up to a zero.

16:47.507 --> 16:50.608
I've been up there.
That place is<i> full</i> of zeroes.

16:50.610 --> 16:52.477
You know,
you<i> are</i> too hip for the room.

16:52.479 --> 16:53.878
Yeah.

16:53.880 --> 16:55.480
Well, uh, thanks.

16:55.482 --> 16:56.714
I'll see you
at lunch, Joe.

16:56.716 --> 16:58.016
Okay.
Hey, wait, wait.

16:58.018 --> 17:00.184
You actually
wanted to be a comedian?

17:00.186 --> 17:01.619
Then what's the job you get
after that?

17:01.621 --> 17:02.987
Like, a talk show host?

17:02.989 --> 17:04.622
Sure. Why not?

17:04.624 --> 17:06.224
You get to talk
to beautiful women,

17:06.226 --> 17:07.325
you sit behind a desk,

17:07.327 --> 17:09.961
and you work, what,
an hour a day?

17:10.897 --> 17:12.497
You're right.

17:12.499 --> 17:15.133
That's some kind of job.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.135
You'd have to be an idiot

17:17.137 --> 17:19.404
to walk away
from that kind of job.

17:22.842 --> 17:26.177
Still better than being stuck
on some stupid sitcom.

17:26.179 --> 17:29.714
♪♪

17:29.716 --> 17:31.783
[ Knock on door ]

17:47.233 --> 17:48.332
Hi.
[ Imitates laser fire ]

17:48.334 --> 17:49.400
Oh. Okay.

17:49.402 --> 17:51.169
What are you doing here?

17:51.171 --> 17:52.570
I mean, I know
we didn't have dinner plans

17:52.572 --> 17:55.106
'cause we're never
doing that again.

17:55.108 --> 17:57.508
Come on.
You and me are going out.

17:57.510 --> 17:58.776
What are you doing?

17:58.778 --> 18:01.345
Something fun,
with my sister.

18:01.347 --> 18:03.948
Look, Ryan told Kyle
and Kyle told me

18:03.950 --> 18:05.216
that you were upset.

18:05.218 --> 18:08.252
There was a lot
of "Marvel vs. DC" talk,

18:08.254 --> 18:09.454
but I got the picture.

18:09.456 --> 18:11.355
It's 8:00.
I can't --

18:13.259 --> 18:15.226
oh, my god.
It's so early.

18:15.228 --> 18:16.127
[ Laughs ]

18:16.129 --> 18:17.628
Holla!

18:17.630 --> 18:21.299
Okay. Rule 1 --
you can't say "holla!"

18:21.301 --> 18:23.401
Oh.
So now<i> you</i> have rules.

18:23.403 --> 18:24.569
Just that one.

18:24.571 --> 18:27.271
And you have to be willing
to get a little crazy.

18:27.273 --> 18:28.739
More importantly,
don't freak out

18:28.741 --> 18:30.641
if<i> I</i> get a little crazy.

18:30.643 --> 18:31.809
Can you handle that?

18:31.811 --> 18:33.144
[ Laughs ]

18:33.146 --> 18:34.412
Yes.

18:34.414 --> 18:37.482
You know,
we're both adults now, so...

18:37.484 --> 18:39.283
Oh, but I have to stop
and get some cash first.

18:39.285 --> 18:42.120
Second rule -- Mandy
and her hot friend never pay.

18:43.123 --> 18:44.222
I'm your hot friend?

18:44.224 --> 18:45.490
Try to act
like you've been there before.

18:45.492 --> 18:48.759
Now, let's go find a cute top
to go with those mom jeans, eh?

18:48.761 --> 18:50.294
Hey!
Come on.

18:50.296 --> 18:52.396
♪♪

18:52.398 --> 18:54.599
Hey, there.
How was accounting?

18:54.601 --> 18:55.600
Learn anything?

18:55.602 --> 18:57.502
Uh, don't shoot dice
with them.

18:57.504 --> 18:59.170
Those guys are sharp.

18:59.172 --> 19:02.907
When did my store
turn into a casino?

19:04.277 --> 19:06.244
Look, I know
you guys have been anxious

19:06.246 --> 19:08.279
for me to make a decision
about college,

19:08.281 --> 19:10.681
so, uh,
I've been thinking.

19:10.683 --> 19:12.316
Yeah?
Did you make a choice?

19:12.318 --> 19:13.184
I did.

19:13.186 --> 19:14.452
I'd like to take
some time off

19:14.454 --> 19:16.420
to figure out
what I want to do with my life.

19:16.422 --> 19:18.489
[ Sighs ]
Eve, I just --

19:18.491 --> 19:21.292
I just think that's a waste of time.
No, it's not.

19:21.294 --> 19:23.294
I want to try different jobs,
do different things,

19:23.296 --> 19:25.029
see if there's something good
that finds me.

19:25.031 --> 19:26.230
Mike?

19:27.534 --> 19:29.133
I think
it's a good idea.

19:29.135 --> 19:30.268
You do?!

19:30.270 --> 19:32.036
I think if you search,
you're gonna find

19:32.038 --> 19:33.437
that you're good
at a<i> lot</i> of things.

19:33.439 --> 19:34.939
I hope.

19:36.943 --> 19:40.278
Calm down. Calm down.

19:40.280 --> 19:42.647
Honey, honey. Come on.
She's in a weird place.

19:42.649 --> 19:44.348
Give her some time.
She'll come around.

19:44.350 --> 19:45.883
I hope so.
"Take some time off"?

19:45.885 --> 19:48.386
It's only our child
and her future.

19:48.388 --> 19:51.322
Vanessa, if you'll recall,
<i> I</i> took a year off.

19:51.324 --> 19:54.292
Yeah. And just think
of what you might have become.

20:02.368 --> 20:03.834
♪♪

20:03.836 --> 20:06.003
Hey, Mike Baxter here
for Outdoor Man.

20:06.005 --> 20:08.039
People often ask me,
say, "hey, Mike.

20:08.041 --> 20:11.242
What are you hoping to find
out there in the wild?"

20:11.244 --> 20:13.044
Maybe just a quiet place

20:13.046 --> 20:16.380
where I don't get asked
annoying questions.

20:16.382 --> 20:18.149
You know, I think
most outdoor types

20:18.151 --> 20:21.919
are continuing the lifelong
search for who we really are.

20:21.921 --> 20:23.487
And let me tell you --

20:23.489 --> 20:25.690
if you think you've figured out
who you are as a teenager,

20:25.692 --> 20:28.059
you might end up being
a teenager your whole life.

20:28.061 --> 20:29.694
You know,
and I've met those guys.

20:29.696 --> 20:32.663
They keep telling me about
their fantasy football team.

20:32.665 --> 20:33.731
I don't care!

20:33.733 --> 20:36.167
<i> Nobody</i> cares!

20:36.169 --> 20:38.603
I've always been more interested
in late bloomers --

20:38.605 --> 20:39.837
you know, the searchers.

20:39.839 --> 20:41.706
Harland Sanders
kicked around Kentucky

20:41.708 --> 20:43.774
pumping gas
and selling insurance

20:43.776 --> 20:46.043
till he opened
his chicken restaurant at 65

20:46.045 --> 20:49.046
and promptly promoted himself
to colonel.

20:49.048 --> 20:50.548
Because let's face it --

20:50.550 --> 20:54.218
no one's buying a bucket
of chicken from<i> private</i> Sanders.

20:54.220 --> 20:55.920
Laura Ingalls Wilder
didn't write

20:55.922 --> 20:58.856
"Little House on the Prairie"
until she, too, was in her 60s.

20:58.858 --> 21:00.625
You know what she was doing
before that?

21:00.627 --> 21:02.927
Trying to stay<i> alive</i>
on the prairie.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.528
Even in the Bible,

21:04.530 --> 21:07.698
Abraham didn't get that
divine facetime call from god

21:07.700 --> 21:09.800
until he was 75.

21:09.802 --> 21:11.702
But he moved his people
to canaan

21:11.704 --> 21:15.473
and fathered children with both
his wife and his housekeeper.

21:15.475 --> 21:18.309
Boy, simpler times, huh?

21:18.311 --> 21:21.078
So, if you're a young person
who's not exactly sure

21:21.080 --> 21:23.281
where life is taking you,
that's okay.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.283
You know, we can't all be
Barack Obama

21:25.285 --> 21:27.918
and have our first job
be president.
